## Why This Is Asked

This question probes practical diagnostic discipline and concrete mitigations for a real-world, multi-tenant file-watching workload. It emphasizes measurable tracing, safe kernel tuning, and robust rollback procedures.

## Key Concepts

- Inotify vs fanotify event storms
- Per-tenant isolation with cgroup2
- Kernel tunables fs.inotify.* and event quotas
- eBPF-based latency measurement and filtering
- Staged load testing and rollback strategies

## Code Example

```javascript
// Simple token bucket limiter for event bursts (illustrative)
let tokens = 1000;
function allow(n) {
  if (tokens >= n) { tokens -= n; return true; }
  return false;
}
```

